All cleaning steps were performed using native Excel functions (TRIM, PROPER, SUBSTITUTE, DATEVALUE, VLOOKUP, IFERROR, COUNTBLANK, AVERAGEIF) rather than macros, to demonstrate formula-based data cleaning skills.
Dashboard
The final dashboard includes:
4 KPI tiles: Total Revenue, Total Orders, Average Discount, Average Order Value (AOV) — all built with GETPIVOTDATA so they respond live to slicer filters instead of showing static totals
6 charts: Revenue by Region (bar), Revenue by Category (column), Top 5 Products (bar), Sales Rep Performance (bar), Order Status (pie), Monthly Revenue Trend (column)
4 interactive slicers: Region, Status, Category, Product — connected to every PivotTable so the entire dashboard updates together on any filter
Key Insights
Electronics accounts for roughly 63% of total revenue, making it the dominant category.
Revenue is evenly distributed across all four regions (~25% each: East ₹15.89Cr, West ₹15.87Cr, North ₹15.73Cr, South ₹15.60Cr), indicating no single region drives the business.
Laptop Pro is the single highest-revenue product at ₹28.2Cr, more than double the next closest product (Standing Desk at ₹13Cr).
Average Order Value (AOV) is ₹6,726, with an average discount rate of 9.45% across all orders.
Order status breakdown: 37% Completed, 38% Pending, 25% Cancelled — a 25% cancellation rate is a notable area for business follow-up.
Sales rep performance is well balanced across the team (Bob Smith and David Lee marginally ahead), with no single rep dominating order volume or revenue.
February and November data is incomplete due to the removal of rows with impossible dates — noted as a data limitation rather than hidden.
Technical note on KPI tiles
Initial KPI tiles used static cell references (e.g. =pivots!B15), which broke when slicers filtered the underlying pivots — the tiles either froze on the unfiltered total or returned incorrect partial sums. This was fixed by switching to GETPIVOTDATA(), which dynamically reads the pivot's current filtered value rather than a fixed cell address.
